<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:my="http://example.com/my" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_īwmæ" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>īwmæ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ewmæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>вместе</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>together</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_īwmæ." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>īwmæ næ rambyrd kæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>собери нас вместе</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>get us together</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>39</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>īwmæjag</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>общий</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>mutual</q></cit></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>īwmæ næ rambyrd kæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>собери нас вместе</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>get us together</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>39</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>īwmæjag</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>общий</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>mutual</q></cit></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Направительный падеж от <xr><ref target="#entry_īw"/></xr> | %iew%i ‘один’, лексикализовавшийся в наречном значении. Точно такое же образование в %bгрузинском:%b<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ertad</w><gloss><q>вместе</q></gloss></mentioned> — направительный падеж от %ierti%i ‘один’. Употребляясь послеложно, %iīwmæ%i стало падежным формантом совместного падежа: %i-imæ%i из %iīwmæ%i (<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">An allative case from <xr><ref target="#entry_īw"/></xr> | %iew%i ‘one’, lexicalized in the adverbial meaning. The same formation is attested in <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ertad</w><gloss><q>together</q></gloss></mentioned> — it is an allative case from %ierti%i ‘one’. Being used as a postposition, %iīwmæ%i became a case marker of comitative case: %i-imæ%i from %iīwmæ%i (<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl>).</etym></entry>